text.tspan: * Presented speaches about typography features in Inkscape, the Google Webfonts project, and the software
freedom movement to graphics design students in several design schools across Argentina (Buenos Aires,
Cordoba and Rosrio) together with Dave Crossland and Pablo Impallari.
* Patches to improve GNOME3's Shell Recorder and prototyping of a screencasting application for GNOME.
* Development of typography related features in Inkscape such as the new Measurement Tool introduced in
* Prototyping of a Firefox add-on for downloading WebFonts
The website is known as Amara.org nowadays. Amara is a featured project of Mozilla Drumbeat,
and the Mozilla Foundation has provided development support.
